Example table:

student_course
-------------------------
student_id
course_id
enrolled_date

Here the primary key = student_id + course_id.

This means the combination must be unique.

Used in Spring Data JPA and Hibernate ORM.

Two Ways to Create Composite PK in JPA

1️⃣ @IdClass
2️⃣ @EmbeddedId

1️⃣ Using @IdClass
Step 1 — Primary Key Class
import java.io.Serializable;

public class StudentCourseId implements Serializable {

    private Integer studentId;
    private Integer courseId;

}
Step 2 — Entity Class
import jakarta.persistence.*;

@Entity
@IdClass(StudentCourseId.class)
public class StudentCourse {

    @Id
    private Integer studentId;

    @Id
    private Integer courseId;

    private String enrolledDate;

}

Now the primary key is:

studentId + courseId
2️⃣ Using @EmbeddedId (Recommended)
Step 1 — Embeddable Key Class
import jakarta.persistence.Embeddable;
import java.io.Serializable;

@Embeddable
public class StudentCourseId implements Serializable {

    private Integer studentId;
    private Integer courseId;

}
Step 2 — Entity Class
import jakarta.persistence.*;

@Entity
public class StudentCourse {

    @EmbeddedId
    private StudentCourseId id;

    private String enrolledDate;

}
Table Structure
student_course
-------------------------
student_id  (PK)
course_id   (PK)
enrolled_date
